gomodel:SYNGO_2359  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: In this paper CSPalpha is shown to regulate the protein stability of SNAP25. This activity is mediated by Hsc70 and SGT.\n\nFig.5: \"CSPα binds to monomeric SNAP-25 through Hsc70.\"\nFig.6: \"The CSPα-Hsc70-SGT complex chaperones SNAP-25 and enhances its incorporation into SNARE complexes in vitro.\"\n\n29/01/2018 Pim\n- Although the data in Fig.6 show the direct role of SGT-alpha (small glutamine-rich tetratricopeptide repeat protein alpha) in the chaperoning in a cell free system. The relevance for and occurence in vivo is suggested by the IP data in Fig.5. Here SNAP-25 IP resulted in selective CSPα, Hsc70 and SGT or SNARE proteins pulldown from brain homogenates.\n- Effects on synaptic transmission is not shown in these or other data since the CSP KO is lethal. A role in SV exocytosis is proposed by the authors. This may be a reasonable inference, but I decided not to annotate to term 'regulation of synaptic vesicle exocytosis'.. Experimental description: Fig.5: \"Immunoprecipitation analysis of protein complexes in the brain of wild-type mice.\"\n- Species of overexpressed protein Hsc70 not stated in the paper." , "Automated change 2025-04-10: GO:0061077 replaced by GO:0006457" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7351-8706" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-3185-5709" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0755-5899" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0938-8534" ;
        dc:date           "2025-04-10" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_2359" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

